cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.HC 

The paper proposes an extension of the TAMER framework that leverages deep neural networks to learn complex tasks with human input. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep learning also suggests that the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category may be relevant. The paper also discusses the application of the proposed method to the Atari game of Bowling, which suggests that the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category may be relevant. Finally, the use of human input in the learning process suggests that the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category may also be relevant.
